definitions.definition: Lacking a voice , without vocal sound.
Without a vote ; having no input into a decision .
Spoken without vibration of the vocal cords ; unvoiced , surd , breathed . Examples: [t], [s], [f], [m̥], [u̥].
definitions.label_groups: phonetics , of a consonant or vowel

main_definition: Lacking a voice , without vocal sound.
secondary_definitions: ( figurative ) Without a vote ; having no input into a decision .
( phonetics , of a consonant or vowel ) Spoken without vibration of the vocal cords ; unvoiced , surd , breathed . Examples: [t], [s], [f], [m̥], [u̥].
